casebody.data:
Gregory STIENS, Appellant,
v.
DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE AND DIVISION OF EMPLOYMENT SECURITY, Respondent. WD 81738 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: February 19, 2019 Gregory Stiens, Appellant Pro-se. Daryl R. Taylor, Kansas City, for Respondent Missouri Department of Agriculture. Before Division One: Cynthia L. Martin, Presiding Judge, Victor C. Howard, Judge and Thomas H. Newton, Judge ORDER PER CURIAM:

Gregory Stiens appeals the decision of the Labor and Industrial Relations Commission ("Commission") affirming the Appeal Tribunal's determination that he was disqualified from receiving unemployment benefits based on his discharge for misconduct connected with work. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum has been provided to the parties. The decision is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
